$interpreted: Joo-Won: Sorry to make you wait.
Scared Girl: Their leader is here, marked on this map.
Joo-Won: Thank you, we'll take care of this.
Scared Girl: Just you two?
Scared Girl: That's the Bloodfang's main base! You'll die!
Joo-Won: Don't worry, the Night Wanderer has the strength of one hundred men. We won't lose, right, Night Wanderer?
Yao: Let's go.
Joo-Won: Cold as ever...
Joo-Won: Alright, let's go.
Joo-Won's Wife: Be careful.
Joo-Won: Look at all of them... I bet their leader is definitely here.
Joo-Won: This is the only road, what's our plan?
Yao: We end them.
Joo-Won: Sounds good to me.
Joo-Won: Maybe we should have been a bit quieter coming here.
Yao: Or maybe we should just quiet them down.
Bloodfang Killer: Leader, they're...
Yao: Here.
Bloodfang Leader: And there you are.
Yao: That calm demeanor... suitable for a leader.
Bloodfang Leader: Well, you are two weaklings. Why would I panic?
Joo-Won: Maybe you should fight us before declaring us weaklings.
Bloodfang Leader: Hah. Why do you think you're still standing here before me?
Bloodfang Leader: It's only because I am allowing you to do so.
Bloodfang Leader: That said, I've enjoyed watching you make your way to my base. Why not join the Bloodfangs?
Joo-Won: I do not side with evil.
Bloodfang Leader: Bwahaha, I figure you'd say something like that. What a delusional little scoundrel.
Bloodfang Leader: Let me tell you something... there is no justice in this world! Only advantage and disadvantage!
Bloodfang Leader: If there is an opportunity, you better believe people like us are going to take it!
Joo-Won: Nonsense.
Bloodfang Leader: Nonsense, hmm? Maybe you should ask your cohort here.
Bloodfang Leader: Looking at his eyes, I can tell he knows all about true humanity.
Yao: I agree with you... humanity is immoral.
Joo-Won: Night Wanderer!?
Yao: But that has nothing to do with why we're here.
Yao: Now, I've had enough of your blabbering.
Bloodfang Leader: Insolent fool.
Joo-Won: Why don't you just give up now?
Bloodfang Leader: Hah! You think you've won?
Bloodfang Leader: Wrong! You lost long before you set foot in my base.
Bloodfang Leader: Gyagh! My hand!!
Yao: Don't think I'll be giving you another chance.
Bloodfang Leader: Hmph, you're a quick one... Too bad I've got something else up my sleeve.
Bloodfang Leader: I hear you have a wife back home, oh righteous one.
Joo-Won: H-How could you know that!?
Bloodfang Leader: Yes, back at your village... What's it called again? Ripple Village?
Joo-Won: You shouldn't know about Ripple Village!
Yao: Unless...!?
Bloodfang Leader: You're too hospitable for your own good, fool!
Yao: This... it's Ripple Village!
Bloodfang Leader: The moment she got there, she sent me word of its location.
Joo-Won: Why!? She helped us!
Bloodfang Leader: SHe only did that to save her own life!!
Yao: Shut up!
Bloodfang Leader: Gyagh! It's useless... there's still... one more letter...
Yao: Don't look!
Joo-Won: That officer we apprehended... has been set free by the Alliance!? Why!?
Bloodfang Leader: I suppose I should tell you some good news. I told him about Ripple Village, too.
Bloodfang Leader: I wonder what he'll do with that information, given how well you treated him?
Joo-Won: N-No!!
Bloodfang Leader: If you quit now, I might still have time to call them off.
Joo-Won: I... No... but...
Joo-Won: Night Wanderer... I can't...
Yao: Leave this to me. You go back for your wife.
Joo-Won: But...
Yao: Go!!
Bloodfang Leader: Wrong move.
Yao: Shut... the... hell... up!!
Yao: Even if I let you go, things would end up the same.
Bloodfang Leader: Bwahaha~! You really are a quick one... and yet, you're still too late.
Yao: And yet justice...
Yao: is always right on time!
Yao: Damn... it's all my fault for being so naive about all of this... thinking things could change.
Yu: Prince Yao.
Yao: It's you... Tell them if they want to punish me to just get it over with. I won't run away.
Yu: ...You're lucky you're important, you get to keep your life. But your cohorts and their families won't be so lucky.
Yao: What did you just say!?
Yu: Someone has to pay for your crimes!
Yu: I will carry out my orders to eliminate all traitors to the Alliance!
Yu: Their families, too.
Yao: Stop that, their families are innocent!
Yu: It must be this way, for military morale and stability!
Yao: Stop right there! I've committed these crimes, not them! If you want to punish someone, punish me! Kill me!
Yao: Come back here! Come back here right now! Don't you dare touch their families, damnit!!
